::Battera:;

She looked inside at the room.  It looked more like a well dressed 
prison cell to her. She turned and looked at Chordate. "Thank you 
again. Here, as a sign of trust." She pulled a long bladed dagger out 
of her wing sheath. "Take this and know I have only one left for 
protection." SHe turned and walked into the room.  She could have 
banged her head against the wall for giving up her only other blade 
and letting him know that she had only one blade left on her. She 
felt like a fool for just walking into the room.  She had to help 
Vulois, but she still felt foolish for being stupidly honest. It left 
her at a disadvantage. And she knew it.
